fu.keys

Class LSIConstants

  • java.lang.Object
    • fu.keys.LSIConstants

  • public class LSIConstants
extends java.lang.Object
    This class only containts constants to LSI class numbers. Using constants in contrast to the number increases readibility. More important, numbers may shifted in the future because new LSI classes are introduces. Using the raw numbers, a program may fail in the futures. Thus, we strongly encourage to use the constants. Note there are three ways to map LSI class tokens to LSI class numbers:
    • using this class, e.g. LSIConstants.BUILDING
    • using a Token to number mapping in LSIClassCentre, e.g. LSIClassCentrelsiClassByToken("BUILDING").lsiClass
    • using a Token to number mapping in LSIClassCentreLight, e.g. LSIClassCentreLight.lsiClass("BUILDING")
    An application can use either way. Please note, that the first way requires a Java constant name, whereas the other mappings map a string at runtime.
